      "summary": "The Come-at-a-Body is a fearsome critter defined by its direct, aggressive behavior.",
      "full": "The Come-at-a-Body is a fearsome critter defined by its direct, aggressive behavior. Unlike stealthy predators or cunning hunters, this creature has one simple strategy: it comes straight at you. No hiding, no ambush, no strategy—just a relentless frontal charge toward anyone it encounters. The name itself uses dialectical English, where \\\"body\\\" means \\\"person\\\" (as in \\\"a body could get hurt\\\" meaning \\\"a person could get hurt\\\"). The creature literally comes at a body—directly, aggressively, inevitably."
